MARCH
  Move land units along a path through your territory.

SYNTAX
  march <unit-spec> <path> [<start-x,y>]

DESCRIPTION
  Moves one or more land units along a sequence of direction steps.
  Units must have sufficient mobility to complete the path.

  <unit-spec>  - land unit number, range (0-5), or * for all
  <path>       - string of direction letters
  [start-x,y]  - optional; overrides unit's current location

  Direction letters:
    u  upper-right      j  right
    n  lower-right      b  lower-left
    g  left             y  upper-left
    h  stop (halt)      v  view (look around)

  Units can only march through sectors you own or have right-of-way
  through.  Marching costs mobility; higher-tech units use less.

  Land units can attack sectors if they march into enemy territory
  (use info attack for a deliberate assault).

EXAMPLE
  march * jj                move all land units right twice
  march 0 njj               move unit 0: lower-right, right, right
  march 0-3 g               move units 0 through 3 left one step

